arch:property.oc:show_val: Small unit that has a fairly high proportion of identifiable bone. The surfaces of the bone are very well preserved, very little weathering has occurred. Species represented are sheep/goat, equid and cattle. NR 2006: Flotation samples have surfaced. Sample 1 >4mm flotation 100% sorted, recorded completely. It is a moderate size sample with moderate fragmentation. Ca. 10% burning, some digestion. Surface condition mostly good. Mostly sheep-size with some large mammal. Few diagnostics here, all of them sheep/goat. Looks like a bit of midden. Sample 9 >4mm flotation 100% sorted, recorded as diagnostics and flot frags only,. This sample is much smaller, but otherwise fairly similar. However, only one of the four diagnostics is sheep/goat. There are two digested dog-size carnivore foot bits, and a digested fox tooth. Obviously all of this says more about the origin of the dog poop than the unit per se.
